input.description: The name of the adapter. Default Name: NetAppActor
The version of the NetApp DFM application. Supported version is: v4.0

Supported item types are:
1. update-dataset 2. dataset-add-resource-pool 3. dataset-remove-resource-pool 4. dataset-resize-member 5. update-protection-policy 6. update-provisioning-policy 7. update-resource-pool 8. resource-pool-add-member 9. resource-pool-remove-member 10. update-resource-pool-members 11. dataset-add-member 12. dataset-remove-member 13. update-dataset-node 14. update-nas-dataset-node 15. update-san-dataset-node 16. update-nfs-security 17. update-cifs-security 18. update-custom-field 19. set-custom-field-value 20. update-vfiler-template 21. add-initiator-to-igroup 22. remove-initiator-from-igroup 23. rename-igroup 24. map-lun-to-igroup 25. unmap-lun-from-igroup

Appropriate Items XML for the request that needs to be executed depending upon the item type.
For ex. If Update Resource Pool needs to be executed sample items XML would be:
<items> <item> <resourcepool-name-or-id>test1</resourcepool-name-or-id> <aggregate-nearly-overcommitted-threshold>70</aggregate-nearly-overcommitted-threshold> <aggregate-overcommitted-threshold>80</aggregate-overcommitted-threshold> <resource-tag>test123</resource-tag> <resourcepool-contact>test@abc.com</resourcepool-contact> <resourcepool-description>test desc123</resourcepool-description> <resourcepool-full-threshold>90</resourcepool-full-threshold> <resourcepool-name>new123</resourcepool-name> <resourcepool-nearly-full-threshold>95</resourcepool-nearly-full-threshold> <resourcepool-owner>test</resourcepool-owner> <resourcepool-timezone>GMT</resourcepool-timezone> </item> </items>
